The paper discusses the use of network traffic analytics technology in cyber security systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of state-of-the-art techniques such as statistical features and correlation analytics, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper emphasizes the need to improve the performance and practicability of automatic traffic analytics, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
